[<p>NEW YORK (Reuters) \u2013 Republican presidential nominee Donald Trump has pulled nearly even with Democratic rival Hillary Clinton for the first time since May, according to a Reuters/Ipsos poll taken over the course of the Republican National Convention in Cleveland this week.</p>, <p>The July 18-22 national online poll found that 41 percent of likely voters supported Clinton, while 38 percent supported Trump. Given the poll\u2019s credibility interval of about 4 percentage points, Trump and Clinton should be considered to be about even in the race.</p>, <p>Just before Republicans opened the convention on Monday, Trump had trailed Clinton by nearly 10 percentage points in the poll.</p>, <p>The New York businessman-turned-politician formally accepted the Republican nomination for the Nov. 8 presidential election during a convention at which the party at times struggled to show unity.</p>]